.TH hsh 1 "August 2025" "0.1" "Simple Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command line interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.RI [ no\ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple UNIX command line interpreter written in C.

It provides a minimal shell interface that executes commands read
from the standard input in either interactive or non-interactive mode.

.SH FEATURES
The shell provides the following features:

.IP \[bu] 2
Display a prompt and wait for the user to type a command.
.IP \[bu]
Execute simple commands with or without arguments.
.IP \[bu]
Handle the
.B PATH
environment variable to locate executables.
.IP \[bu]
Provide built-in commands:
.RS
.IP \[em] 4
.B exit
– exit the shell.
.IP \[em]
.B env
– print the current environment.
.RE
.IP \[bu]
Handle end of file (Ctrl+D).
.IP \[bu]
Provide error messages in the same format as
.B /bin/sh .

.SH USAGE
.B Interactive mode:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ./hsh
($) /bin/ls
file1 file2 file3
($) exit
.fi
.RE

.B Non-interactive mode:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
file1 file2 file3
.fi
.RE

.SH EXIT STATUS
The shell returns the exit status of the last executed command.
If a command cannot be found, the exit status is
.B 127 .
If a command fails, the exit status is
.B 2 .
A successful command returns
.B 0 .

.SH FILES
.TP
.B main.c
entry point of the shell.
.TP
.B execute_command.c
execution of commands using fork and execve.
.TP
.B split_line.c
splits the user input into tokens.
.TP
.B get_path.c
handles path resolution.
.TP
.B utils.c
helper functions.
.TP
.B hsh.h
header file with prototypes.
.TP
.B man_simple_shell
this manual page.

.SH AUTHOR
Written by Alba Eftimi.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh (1),
.BR bash (1),
.BR execve (2)
